Hello everyone. I am once again in Anthropology. And once again bored. And once again thinking that maybe I should just change my major to something that I won't fall asleep studying. 
Life is good. Actually it is really good. changes are acomin and I am really happy about it. 
I am worried about money and school next year. but i know no matter what happens I will survive. 
I am moving to WSU that much I know.. yay. 
Which means in a year I will be a resident of Washington. Woo. 
I have been having these really weird dreams about someone from my past and I dont get as to why i am dreaming about them. hmm being a witch is confusing.. hahahaha
other than that like i have said life is great. I miss some of my old life but i know this change is good. 
I wish all of you the best.

So all day -in between Napping- I have been watching my stock pile of movies made out of this country. Yes I actually have cultured tastes! 

Anyway I have decided that I really don't enjoy were I am at this point in my life not specifically the geography but school and my loss of patience with someone that I love. (a friend nothing more .. oy!) 

I want to change I want to move I want to stir the air around me and push my limits. I want to be thrown into something new. I am watching my favorite movie and I think I want to study abroad in India. I want to go through the private school that My sister works for and move to India for a year and study with monks and The Dalhi Lama. I want to learn about this culture. While I am there I want to travel in the middle east, see Iran, Pakistan, Saudi Arabia, Tibet, Nepal, Everything. My sister and brother in law have plans to go to europe after she gets her PHD and I think I will meet them and we will go around europe. 

I want this more than anything. I want to be myself before I am anyone's fortune teller, girlfriend, Class mate. I want to have this experience. So badly that it hurts.

 
in the end...I WANNA GET OUT OF THIS FUCKING COUNTRY GAHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH

Packing your life into a box
Isn't as fun as once thought
putting away your past
entraping your childhood
saying goodbye to 
people that love you 
throwing away stories
boxing up 
your toys 
that crown that made you a princess 
that wand that made you a powerful witch
stop dancing to that music
there is no audience amazed at your moves 
and certainly not there for your voice
packing your life away into a box
sure i am a grown women now
I have trapped my past 
in a cardboard prison
and I dare to venture
am i ready for this?
